      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's all about the Black and Latino youth, specifically from the inner cities and urban neighborhoods. You can't replicate the \"street\" look without embracing the authentic styles and attitudes of these communities. Think of the likes of New York City's Harlem, Brooklyn, and the Bronx, or Los Angeles's Compton and South Central. The core group driving these trends right now are the young, working-class men of color who are unapologetically themselves, with a mix of athletic and streetwear influences. You should be looking to capture the essence of these communities, not just some watered-down, superficial interpretation.",
      "source": "target",
